  <h4 class="pHead4" >
</h4>    

<a name="wp3695100"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
Notes
</h3>    

<a name="wp3695101"> </a><p class="pNumber" >
 1.	By default, the <code class="cCodeBody">assert_one_hot</code> assertion is optimistic and the assertion fails if <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">test_expr</span> is zero or has multiple bits not set to 0 (i.e.equals 1, X, Z, etc.). However, if &#8216;OVL_XCHECK_OFF is set, the ASSERT_ONE_HOT assertion fails if and only if <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">test_expr</span> is zero or has multiple bits that are 1.
</p>    
<a name="wp3695102"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
See also
</h3>    

